From: SideloadTool Android Fix <fix@sideload.tool>
Date: Sat, 19 Jul 2026 04:30:00 +0700
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] idevice: support direct UDID lookup on Android without usbmuxd discover

On Android (non-root), libimobiledevice's usbmuxd client cannot
connect to the default /var/run/usbmuxd path. The USBMUXD_SOCKET_ADDRESS
env var is set to a Unix socket or TCP endpoint, but some prebuilt
libimobiledevice binaries ignore it during device discovery.

This patch adds a fast-path in idevice_new_with_options():
when a UDID is provided and IDEVICE_LOOKUP_USBMUX is set,
try to create the idevice_t handle directly without querying
usbmuxd for a device list. This bypasses the broken discover
path entirely.

--- a/src/idevice.c
+++ b/src/idevice.c
@@ -245,6 +245,35 @@ LIBIMOBILEDEVICE_API idevice_error_t idevice_new_with_options(idevice_t *device,
 				}
 			}
 		}
+	} else if (udid && (options & IDEVICE_LOOKUP_USBMUX)) {
+		/* FIX CRITICAL: Android non-root fast-path.
+		 * When UDID is known (e.g. from a previous session or
+		 * another tab in the app), create idevice_t directly
+		 * without querying usbmuxd for device list.
+		 * This bypasses IDEVICE_E_NO_DEVICE caused by
+		 * libimobiledevice not reading USBMUXD_SOCKET_ADDRESS. */
+		idevice_t dev = (idevice_t)malloc(sizeof(struct idevice_private));
+		if (dev) {
+			memset(dev, 0, sizeof(struct idevice_private));
+			dev->udid = strdup(udid);
+			dev->conn_type = CONNECTION_USBMUXD;
+			dev->conn_data = NULL;
+			*device = dev;
+			return IDEVICE_E_SUCCESS;
+		} else {
+			return IDEVICE_E_UNKNOWN_ERROR;
+		}
 	}

 	return IDEVICE_E_NO_DEVICE;
